Furthermore, to obtain 0.7 ± 0.02 units at 734 nm as absorption, the solution was diluted with ethanol. Samples were separately dissolved in ethanol to yield the following concentrations: (0.312, 0.625, 1.25, 2.5, and 5 mg/mL). In order to measure the essential oil antioxidant activity, 10 μL were added to 990 μL of diluted ABTS·+at various concentrations. The absorption was read after 20 min of incubation. The antioxidant power of each sample was expressed as the inhibition percentage (I %) calculated according to the following formula:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
